# Paperboard — GitHub Copilot Coding Agent Instructions

Integrate `atv-paperboard` into your Copilot Coding Agent workflow to auto-render
structured outputs as self-contained HTML artifacts governed by a `DESIGN.md`.

## When to invoke `paperboard render`

Invoke after any tool writes a file that matches **one or more** of these patterns:

| Trigger | Examples |
|---------|---------|
| Status dashboards | Build status table, CI results matrix, test pass/fail grid |
| Comparison tables | Model benchmarks, A/B experiment results, feature comparisons |
| Output viewers | LLM evaluation sheets, structured JSON summaries, scoring rubrics |
| Data tables with ≥2 numeric columns | Performance metrics, cost breakdowns, load test results |
| Markdown files with `status`/`score`/`result`/`count` column headers | Any agent-generated report |

## How to invoke

```bash
paperboard render --input <path-to-file> [--tier pico|daisy] [--no-open]
```

Pass `--no-open` in CI / headless environments.

## After rendering

Run `paperboard gallery` to refresh the local artifact index at `paperboard-artifacts/gallery.html`.

## Do NOT invoke for

- Pure prose documentation (README, CHANGELOG, design docs)
- Files in `.github/`, `docs/`, or `node_modules/`
- Files the render step itself produces (self-recursion guard)

## Harness detection

`paperboard` auto-detects the harness. No configuration needed when running under
GitHub Copilot Coding Agent (resolves to `copilot` harness, writes to `paperboard-artifacts/`).
